pip: 
    create venv on window 
    `python -m venv venv --without-pip`

    create venv on ubuntu 
    `virtualenv venv `

    activate the window server policy on powershell
    `Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope Process` 

    run python enviroment
    `.\venv\Scripts\activate`

    freeze requirements
    `pip freeze > requirements.txt`

    install package from textfile
    `pip install -r requirements.txt`

    generate a list of all outdated packages
    `pip list --outdated`

    update a list of all outdated packages
    `pip list --outdated --format=freeze | grep -v '^\-e' | cut -d = -f 1 | xargs -n1 pip install -U`

django: 
    migrate data only first time
    `python manage.py migrate`

    create session after create new model
    `python manage.py migrate sessions`

    add super user
    `python manage.py createsuperuser` or 
    `python manage.py createsuperuser --email root@example.com --username root`

    start server in docker with no reload because reduce cpu overload
    `python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000 --noreload`

    * when update new model run command
    `python manage.py makemigrations`

    * when has new file for makemigration run 
    `python manage.py migrate`

    **when start new project use for setup project
    `django-admin startproject base .`    

    use for create structure build code
    `django-admin startapp core`

scrapy:
    install scrapy project
    `scrapy startproject dbdv2`